trans-unit.source: Assigns data to clusters using an existing trained clustering model
trans-unit.target: Assigns data to clusters using an existing trained clustering model

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module to generate predictions using a trained clustering model, based on the K-Means clustering algorithm included in Azure Machine Learning.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module to generate predictions using a trained clustering model, based on the K-Means clustering algorithm included in Azure Machine Learning.

trans-unit.source: The module returns the probable assignments for each new data point, based on the trained model.
trans-unit.target: The module returns the probable assignments for each new data point, based on the trained model.

trans-unit.source: How to Use Assign to Clusters
trans-unit.target: How to Use Assign to Clusters

trans-unit.source: Your workspace should contain a trained clustering model created using either the <link xlink:href="5049a09b-bd90-4c4e-9b46-7c87e3a36810" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">K-mean</link> module or a custom clustering algorithm.
trans-unit.target: Your workspace should contain a trained clustering model created using either the <link xlink:href="5049a09b-bd90-4c4e-9b46-7c87e3a36810" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">K-mean</link> module or a custom clustering algorithm.

trans-unit.source: Attach the trained model to the left input port of
trans-unit.target: Attach the trained model to the left input port of

trans-unit.source: You must provide an unlabeled data set as input.
trans-unit.target: You must provide an unlabeled data set as input.

trans-unit.source: By default, all columns that are used in the input dataset are returned in the results.
trans-unit.target: By default, all columns that are used in the input dataset are returned in the results.

trans-unit.source: If you want to use fewer columns when creating cluster predictions, use <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project Columns</link> to select a subset of the columns.
trans-unit.target: If you want to use fewer columns when creating cluster predictions, use <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project Columns</link> to select a subset of the columns.

trans-unit.source: However, the dataset provided as input to the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module must contain <legacyBold>all</legacyBold> columns that were used in training the clustering model, or an error will occur.
trans-unit.target: However, the dataset provided as input to the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module must contain <legacyBold>all</legacyBold> columns that were used in training the clustering model, or an error will occur.

trans-unit.source: The <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module returns the <newTerm>cluster assignments</newTerm> for each case, in the <ui>Assignments</ui> column appended at the right hand side of the dataset.
trans-unit.target: The <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module returns the <newTerm>cluster assignments</newTerm> for each case, in the <ui>Assignments</ui> column appended at the right hand side of the dataset.

trans-unit.source: If you do not want all the columns in the results, select the option to output only the results.
trans-unit.target: If you do not want all the columns in the results, select the option to output only the results.

trans-unit.source: For example, when making predictions as part of a web service you might want to return only the ID and the predicted assignment.
trans-unit.target: For example, when making predictions as part of a web service you might want to return only the ID and the predicted assignment.

trans-unit.source: Choose the columns from the attached dataset that will be provided as input to the trained clustering model.
trans-unit.target: Choose the columns from the attached dataset that will be provided as input to the trained clustering model.

trans-unit.source: If the original models used eight feature columns to cluster cases, you must provide those same eight columns as input to <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui>.
trans-unit.target: If the original models used eight feature columns to cluster cases, you must provide those same eight columns as input to <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Check for Append or Uncheck for Result Only
trans-unit.target: Check for Append or Uncheck for Result Only

trans-unit.source: By default, this option is selected, meaning that the full input dataset is returned, together with a column indicating the results (cluster assignments).
trans-unit.target: By default, this option is selected, meaning that the full input dataset is returned, together with a column indicating the results (cluster assignments).

trans-unit.source: If you deselect this option, you can get back just the results, which is useful in the web service or in applications.
trans-unit.target: If you deselect this option, you can get back just the results, which is useful in the web service or in applications.

trans-unit.source: The <externalLink><linkText>Color quantization </linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525272</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses clustering to group images by color patterns to reduce the number of bits needed to represent each image.
trans-unit.target: The <externalLink><linkText>Color quantization </linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525272</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses clustering to group images by color patterns to reduce the number of bits needed to represent each image.

trans-unit.source: The <externalLink><linkText>Clustering: Similar Companies</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525164</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses clustering with text extracted from Wikipedia description to find companies in predefined categories.
trans-unit.target: The <externalLink><linkText>Clustering: Similar Companies</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=525164</linkUri></externalLink> sample uses clustering with text extracted from Wikipedia description to find companies in predefined categories.

trans-unit.source: Here, K-means clustering was used to group people in the Adult Census dataset, using these columns: <database>workclass</database>, <database>education</database>, <database>occupation</database>, <database>sex</database>.
trans-unit.target: Here, K-means clustering was used to group people in the Adult Census dataset, using these columns: <database>workclass</database>, <database>education</database>, <database>occupation</database>, <database>sex</database>.

trans-unit.source: Then we used the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module to predict which census groups a new data point might belong to, based on similar attributes.
trans-unit.target: Then we used the <ui>Assign to Clusters</ui> module to predict which census groups a new data point might belong to, based on similar attributes.

trans-unit.source: The clusters created by the model are 0-based numeric labels and cannot be edited in Azure Machine Learning Studio.
trans-unit.target: The clusters created by the model are 0-based numeric labels and cannot be edited in Azure Machine Learning Studio.

trans-unit.source: Note that wherever there are missing values in any attribute that was used to train the model (in this case, <database>workclass</database>, a prediction (assignment) will not be generated.
trans-unit.target: Note that wherever there are missing values in any attribute that was used to train the model (in this case, <database>workclass</database>, a prediction (assignment) will not be generated.
